last week=E2=80=94which looks like an effort to slim down to satisfy the bo=
ard and position itself for potential suitors.

And yet, while the company has struggled to grow beyond its founder=E2=80=
=99s polarizing (but not too polarizing) persona, Goop endures because it i=
s, perhaps, the only true celebrity lifestyle brand. Paltrow has managed to=
 annoy and entice in equal measure, serving up self-deprecating grandiosity=
, combined with impeccable taste and an almost-attainable life that you, to=
o, can sample by buying the serum she uses or taking $75 Tracy Anderson gro=
up classes in the Hamptons. Below, Lauren and I discuss why people care abo=
ut Goop so much, how the company lost its way, and what a potential exit co=
uld look like.

